      "title": "The Hourglass Sanatorium (1973)",
      "description": "The Hourglass Sanatorium is a 1973 Polish drama film directed by Wojciech Jerzy Has, starring Jan Nowicki, Tadeusz Kondrat, Mieczysław Voit, Halina Kowalska and Gustaw Holoubek. It is also known as The Sandglass in English-speaking countries. It  follows a young Jewish man named Józef who travels to a mystical sanatorium to visit his dying father. Upon arrival, he discovers a decaying facility where time behaves unpredictably, leading him through a dream-like exploration of his memories and experiences.",
